[recto] VALKENBORCH [sic]. Peasant very thin, 'water verwe' canvas attached to panel but in face oil paint as usual - probably 17th century. Typical figure taken out of context copied from a picture. A few chalk lines in underdrawing lack precision of P.B.I. Brown coat, with red lin[in]g, bluish jacket, grey blue cap, white trousers; [verso] [onleesbaar] VALKENBURG Coll. Dancing Peasant attrib. to Bruegel, 56 1/2 x 45,3 cm. Now with a Mr. Schindler, Brussels. repr. Bastelaer, Hausenstein ; W. Martz, in Oude Kunst in Nederland; Wurzbach III, 1911, p. 40; Exh. Düsseldorf 1904, N° 2093; Boijmans 1913; Gent 1913; Utrecht 1913, N° 1033; Kopenhagen 1925 [sic] [= Udstillingen af Belgisk kunst fra XV.-XX. aarhundrede. I: Ny Carlsberg Glyptotek i Tiden fra 26. April til 25. Maj 1931, Kùbenhavn : Jùrgensen, 1931, nr. 6, fig. p. 51]
